	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Now you hit the heart of the class, range combat.  People who complain that Rangers aren't strong enough need to listen to this.  They can root and deal decent damage, often bringing a mob to death's door before even lifting a blade once.  Also, as of a month or two ago, root and snare work together.  This means that casting while kiting is much easier.  Just root the mob down and shot while casting.  Also, melee timers react correctly with casting.  <BR>
<BR>
If you've heard of multikiting, this is kinda what this spell would be used for, but it's not a good idea to try multikiting with a Ranger, if you can avoid it, becaue they can't do it well enough to survive.  Still if you have a chance to use it, the spell is potent indeed.<BR>
<BR>
May Tunare keep you...<BR>
<BR>
Silvatus Leafwind, the Outrider
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
