	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I'm a level 15 Human Ranger with a Trueshot Bow. This is the better spell for me even one-on-one because of my tactics. I'm a Master Fletcher and currently use Hooked Point, Bone Shaft, Round Fletch, Medium Nock arrows. I root the MoB, send off an arrow, cast Invoke Lightning, shoot another arrow, and cast again usually before the MoB breaks root. All MoBs I fight now are AT LEAST 100 hitpoints down, and most are 120 down when meele starts. I use a PGT (low damage, but awesome proc - 2 times per battle on average) and usually finish a battle with a con even being down only a bubble or so of health. Wizzies have mastered &quot;Root-N-Nuke&quot;, I just applied it to the Ranger using the available tools that I have. I intend to up my Fletching skill a bit more so I can make more powerful arrows and actually try to bring down a MoB without Meele (just for giggles). This method has allowed my to continue fighting con yellow MoBs (Gorge Hounds in EK) without too much worry (I've won 3 of 4 so far - 4th one I was fortunate enough to have a Necro close by who's pet finished it off for me). Using the &quot;Root-N-Shoot&quot; method, max damage is needed, not mana efficiency. I like the method, and I love my Ranger!<BR>
<BR>
Kileria<BR>
Ranger of the 15th Circle<BR>
--== Veeshan Server ==--
				</font>
			</td>

